  "text": "The affinity chromatography experiments suggested that ␣ -and ␤ -dystroglycan are the only abundant rat brain proteins which interact strongly with the neurexin 1 ␣ Ig fusion protein (Fig. 2) . To explore the specificity and tightness of dystroglycan binding to neurexin 1 ␣ , we probed the flowthrough, washes, and high salt eluents of similar affinity chromatography experiments by immunoblotting. These results confirmed that the neurexin 1 ␣ column but not the control column strongly bound ␣ -and ␤ -dystroglycan (Fig.  3) . Strikingly, ␣ -and ␤ -dystroglycan were quantitatively removed from the flow-through of the neurexin 1 ␣ column, demonstrating that dystroglycan binding to neurexin 1 ␣ is of high affinity (Fig. 3, lane 2) . No binding of neuroligin 1 to neurexin 1 ␣ was observed as expected from previous results showing that only ␤ -neurexins bind to neuroligins [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
